The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Double for opener
                                                                                                                       7                                        Double for opener
            OUR CORRESPONDENT            Team India coach Gary Kirsten with son Joshua during a practice session ahead of the third and final Test against Sri Lanka, in Mumbai, on Sunday. (AFP)                           
	Mumbai: Gautam Gambhir bagged the double of International Cricketer and the International Test Batsman of the Year at the Ceat Cricket Ratings Awards here on Sunday.         
	Gambhirs opening partner Virender Sehwag received the one day International (ODI) Batsman of the Year award while Sri Lankas Ajantha Mendis was adjudged the ODI Bowler of the Year. Mendis compatriot Thilan Samaraweera got the Spirit of Cricket award.         
	Australias left-arm speedster Mitchell Johnson was the awarded with the Test Bowler of the Year trophy, while his national team was declared the International Team of the Year.         
	Former Test spinner Erapalli Prasanna was given the International Achievement Award, while Harbhajan Singh was felicitated for crossing the 300 wickets milestone in Tests.                                                                                                                     
